{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"346ee478-c046-4e77-8521-427b8b7b816b","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework Support in MSTest v3:**\n| Target | Compatible? | Issue |\n|---|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Yes | .NET Framework 4.6.2+ is supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ No | .NET 5 is EOL; MSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ No | .NET Core 3.1 is EOL and dropped in MSTest v3 |\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. **Update target frameworks** — replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or later) and drop `netcoreapp3.1`:\n   ```xml\n   <TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n   ```\n\n2. **Replace the two package references** with the single consolidated MSTest package:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n   ```\n   (This replaces both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`.)\n\n3. Keep `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` but consider updating it as well.\n\n**Other breaking changes to watch for** in MSTest v3 include stricter `[TestClass]` enforcement, removal of some deprecated APIs, and new default behaviors for test parallelization. Review the [MSTest v3 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/mstest-sdk-overview) before upgrading.\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes to your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"75494c01-4986-47bc-9544-108474b24972","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has dropped support for some older frameworks. Let me provide a clear analysis.\n\nMSTest v3 key changes:\n- Minimum supported frameworks: .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n- `net5.0` is NOT supported (it's EOL and MSTest v3 requires net6.0+)\n- `netcoreapp3.1` is NOT supported (MSTest v3 dropped support for netcoreapp3.1)\n\n\n- `net462` should work fine since MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above\n\nAlso, MSTest v3 consolidates packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package instead of separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`.","outputTokens":624,"requestId":"0418:38C5AF:16D8128:18489A5:6A033802"},"id":"1928ee8f-9c23-4303-a048-e3546d8f9d47","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:24:18.836Z","parentId":"ceaaee37-b8b4-4ffe-81d4-49138e794534"}
